      "id": "1ddabd6f_0588604d",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/resources/logback-spring.xml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": null,
      "message": "Exact, the base one was including the CONSOLE appender anyway, causing the duplication.\nSee https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/main/spring-boot-project/spring-boot/src/main/resources/org/springframework/boot/logging/logback/base.xml\nThen, we skipped this base one to keep only the defaults include.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2022-05-05 13:29:24.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3c3a4707_d3621825",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c85c2ea6_491237ba",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/resources/logback-spring.xml",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 72,
      "message": "It is enabled at line 63 above. \n\nAsyncAppender is a wrapper on top of either jsonConsole or CONSOLE appender depending on the configuration. The default configuration is specified in application.yml as the json one.\n\nThen, the default `json` value for `logging.format` property can be changed at application startup time to come with the more human readable text format.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2022-05-05 13:29:24.000000000",
